<li><a href="https://www.carlstalhood.com/horizon-view-load-balancing-netscaler-11-1/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Load balance</a>Â your multiple Horizon Connection Servers.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="cert">Horizon Connection Server Certificate</h2>
<ol>
<li>RunÂ <strong>certlm.msc</strong> (Windows 2012+). Or run <strong>mmc</strong>, add the <strong>Certificates</strong> snap-in, and point it to <strong>Computer &gt; Local Machine</strong>.</li>
<li>Request a new certificate with a common name that matches the FQDN of the Connection Server, or import a wildcard certificate.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10703 " src="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce72f8d47fc.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce72f8d47fc.png?w=495&amp;ssl=1 495w, https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce72f8d47fc.png?resize=300%2C140&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 495px) 100vw, 495px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Note: the private key must be exportable. If using the <strong>Computer</strong> template, click <strong>Details</strong>,Â and then click<strong> Properties</strong>.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10704 " src="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7334bc600.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7334bc600.png?w=629&amp;ssl=1 629w, https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7334bc600.png?resize=300%2C195&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 629px) 100vw, 629px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>On the <strong>Private Key</strong> tab, click <strong>Key options</strong> to expand it, and check the box next to <strong>Mark private key as exportable</strong>.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10705 " src="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce73502d6e5.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce73502d6e5.png?w=502&amp;ssl=1 502w, https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce73502d6e5.png?resize=300%2C227&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 502px) 100vw, 502px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>In the list of certificates, look for the one that is self-signed. The Issuer will be the local computer name instead of a Certificate Authority. Right-click it, and click <strong>Properties</strong>.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10706 " src="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7378265c2.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7378265c2.png?w=585&amp;ssl=1 585w, https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7378265c2.png?resize=300%2C183&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>On the <strong>General</strong> tab, clear the <em>Friendly name</em> field, and click <strong>OK</strong>.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10707 " src="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7392beb4a.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7392beb4a.png?w=405&amp;ssl=1 405w, https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7392beb4a.png?resize=300%2C164&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 405px) 100vw, 405px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Right-click your Certificate Authority-signed certificate, and try to export it.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10709 " src="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce73d7deecd.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce73d7deecd.png?w=636&amp;ssl=1 636w, https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce73d7deecd.png?resize=300%2C165&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 636px) 100vw, 636px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>On the <em>Export Private Key</em> page, make sureÂ <strong>Yes, export the private key</strong> is selectable. If the option to export the private key is grayed out, then this certificate will not work. Click <strong>Cancel</strong>.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10710 " src="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce73ee7bc0e.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce73ee7bc0e.png?w=535&amp;ssl=1 535w, https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce73ee7bc0e.png?resize=300%2C162&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 535px) 100vw, 535px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Right-click your Certificate Authority-signed certificate, and click <strong>Properties</strong>.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10708 " src="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce73aaa80d3.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce73aaa80d3.png?w=513&amp;ssl=1 513w, https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce73aaa80d3.png?resize=300%2C189&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 513px) 100vw, 513px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>On the <strong>General</strong> tab, in the <em>Friendly name</em> field, enter the text <strong>vdm</strong>, and click <strong>OK</strong>. Note: only one certificate can have <strong>vdm</strong> as the Friendly name.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10711 " src="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce74313c90d.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce74313c90d.png?w=405&amp;ssl=1 405w, https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce74313c90d.png?resize=300%2C130&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 405px) 100vw, 405px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Then restart the <strong>VMware Horizon View Connection Server</strong> service. It will take several seconds before you can connect to Horizon View Administrator.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10712 " src="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7458db962.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7458db962.png?w=553&amp;ssl=1 553w, https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7458db962.png?resize=300%2C178&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 553px) 100vw, 553px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
</ol>
<h2 id="portal">Horizon Portal â€“ Client Installation Link</h2>
<p>If you point your browser to the Horizon Connection Server (without /admin in the path), the <strong>Install VMware Horizon Client</strong> link redirects to the VMware.com site for downloading of Horizon Clients. You can change it so that the Horizon Clients can be downloaded directly from the Horizon Connection Server.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-33108 " src="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/img_5c90000dd665b.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/img_5c90000dd665b.png?w=529&amp;ssl=1 529w, https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/img_5c90000dd665b.png?resize=261%2C300&amp;ssl=1 261w" sizes="(max-width: 529px) 100vw, 529px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></p>
<ol>
<li>On the Horizon Connection Server, go to <strong>C:\Program Files\VMware\VMware View\Server\broker\webapps</strong>.</li>
<li>Create a new folder called <strong>downloads</strong>.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10716 " src="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce79b170fa2.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce79b170fa2.png?w=752&amp;ssl=1 752w, https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce79b170fa2.png?resize=300%2C101&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 752px) 100vw, 752px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Copy the <a href="https://my.vmware.com/web/vmware/info/slug/desktop_end_user_computing/vmware_horizon_clients/5_0" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">downloaded Horizon Client 5.2 for Windows</a>Â to the newÂ <strong>C:\Program Files\VMware\VMware View\Server\broker\webapps</strong><strong>\downloads</strong> folder.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-37674 " src="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d88cab690f02.png?w=1100&#038;ssl=1" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d88cab690f02.png?w=823&amp;ssl=1 823w, https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d88cab690f02.png?resize=300%2C59&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d88cab690f02.png?resize=768%2C150&amp;ssl=1 768w" sizes="(max-width: 823px) 100vw, 823px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Run Notepad as administrator.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10719 " src="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7a586a629.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7a586a629.png?w=366&amp;ssl=1 366w, https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7a586a629.png?resize=300%2C136&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 366px) 100vw, 366px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Open the fileÂ <strong>C:\ProgramData\VMware\VDM\portal\portal-links-html-access.properties</strong>Â file with a text editor (as Administrator).<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10720 " src="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7a7f8992d.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7a7f8992d.png?w=593&amp;ssl=1 593w, https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7a7f8992d.png?resize=300%2C127&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 593px) 100vw, 593px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Go back to theÂ <strong>downloads</strong>Â folder, and copy the Horizon Client filename.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-37675 " src="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d88caf84bc05.png?w=1100&#038;ssl=1" alt="" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d88caf84bc05.png?w=561&amp;ssl=1 561w, https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d88caf84bc05.png?resize=300%2C128&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 561px) 100vw, 561px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>In Notepad, modify <strong>link</strong>.<strong>win32</strong> and <strong>link.</strong><strong>win64</strong> by specifying the relative path to the Horizon Client executable under <strong>/downloads</strong>. Note: In Horizon Client 4.3 and newer, there&#8217;s only one Horizon client for both 32-bit and 64-bit. The following example shows a link for the Horizon win64 client.
<pre>link.win64=/downloads/VMware-Horizon-Client-5.2.0-14570289.exe</pre>
</li>
<li>Then <strong>Save</strong> the file.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-37676 " src="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d88cb1b9c110.png?w=1100&#038;ssl=1" alt="" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d88cb1b9c110.png?w=684&amp;ssl=1 684w, https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d88cb1b9c110.png?resize=300%2C138&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 684px) 100vw, 684px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Restart the <strong>VMware Horizon View Web Component</strong> service, or restart the entire Connection Server.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10725 " src="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7c20a5b3d.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7c20a5b3d.png?w=541&amp;ssl=1 541w, https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7c20a5b3d.png?resize=300%2C243&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 541px) 100vw, 541px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>It will take a few seconds for the <strong>ws_TomcatService</strong> process to start so be patient. If you get a 503 error, then the service is not done starting.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10727 " src="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7cea3ce22.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7cea3ce22.png?w=468&amp;ssl=1 468w, https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7cea3ce22.png?resize=300%2C115&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 468px) 100vw, 468px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Now when you click the link to download the client, it will grab the file directly from the Horizon Connection Server.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-37677 " src="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d88d1399e443.png?w=1100&#038;ssl=1" alt="" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d88d1399e443.png?w=737&amp;ssl=1 737w, https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d88d1399e443.png?resize=300%2C295&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 737px) 100vw, 737px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Repeat these steps on each Connection Server.</li>
</ol>
<h3 id="portalbranding">Portal Branding</h3>
<p>Chris Tucker atÂ <a href="https://www.definetomorrow.co.uk/blog/2019/1/15/horizon-view-7x-branding-the-logon-pge" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Horizon View 7.X &#8211; Branding the Logon page</a> details how to brand the Horizon 7.1 and newer portal page.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-32482 " src="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/img_5c41cc4db8dbb.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/img_5c41cc4db8dbb.png?w=773&amp;ssl=1 773w, https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/img_5c41cc4db8dbb.png?resize=300%2C256&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/img_5c41cc4db8dbb.png?resize=768%2C656&amp;ssl=1 768w" sizes="(max-width: 773px) 100vw, 773px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></p>
<h2>LDAP Edits</h2>
<h3 id="horizonconsoletimeout">Horizon Console Timeout</h3>
<p>The HTML5 Horizon Console (https://MyConnectionServer<strong>/newadmin</strong>) has a default timeout of 10 minutes. Changing the Horizon Administrator timeout will not affect the Horizon Console timeout. You can use <strong>adsiedit.msc</strong> to increase the Horizon Console timeout.</p>
<ol>
<li>On the Horizon Connection Server, run <strong>ADSI Edit</strong>.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10728 " src="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7d1e94f62.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7d1e94f62.png?w=311&amp;ssl=1 311w, https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7d1e94f62.png?resize=300%2C129&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 311px) 100vw, 311px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Right-click <strong>ADSI Edit</strong>, and clickÂ <strong>Connect to</strong>.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10729 " src="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7d3ebfcb2.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7d3ebfcb2.png?w=345&amp;ssl=1 345w, https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7d3ebfcb2.png?resize=300%2C189&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 345px) 100vw, 345px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Change the first selection to <strong>Select or type a Distinguished Name</strong>, and enter <strong>dc=vdi,dc=vmware,dc=int.</strong></li>
<li>Change the second selection to <strong>Select or type a domain or server</strong>, and enter <strong>localhost</strong>. Click <strong>OK</strong>.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10730 " src="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7d91bc4f8.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7d91bc4f8.png?w=380&amp;ssl=1 380w, https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7d91bc4f8.png?resize=295%2C300&amp;ssl=1 295w" sizes="(max-width: 380px) 100vw, 380px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Navigate to <strong>Properties &gt; Global</strong>. On the right, double-click <strong>CN=Common</strong>.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10731 " src="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7db396670.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7db396670.png?w=510&amp;ssl=1 510w, https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7db396670.png?resize=300%2C294&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 510px) 100vw, 510px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Scroll down, click to highlight <strong>pae-APISessionTimeout</strong>, and click <strong>Edit</strong>.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-37760 " src="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d8d0f2240d47.png?w=1100&#038;ssl=1" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d8d0f2240d47.png?w=400&amp;ssl=1 400w, https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d8d0f2240d47.png?resize=286%2C300&amp;ssl=1 286w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Enter a value in minutes. Click <strong>OK</strong>.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-37759 " src="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d8d0f1241b08.png?w=1100&#038;ssl=1" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d8d0f1241b08.png?w=409&amp;ssl=1 409w, https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/img_5d8d0f1241b08.png?resize=300%2C107&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 409px) 100vw, 409px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
</ol>
<h3 id="savepwd">Mobile Client &#8211; Save Password</h3>
<p>If desired, you can configure Horizon Connection Server to allow mobile clients (iOS, Android) to save user passwords.</p>
<ol>
<li>On the Horizon Connection Server, run <strong>ADSI Edit</strong>.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10728 " src="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7d1e94f62.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7d1e94f62.png?w=311&amp;ssl=1 311w, https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7d1e94f62.png?resize=300%2C129&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 311px) 100vw, 311px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Right-click <strong>ADSI Edit</strong>, and clickÂ <strong>Connect to</strong>.<br/>
