<h3 id="touchid">Biometric Authentication &#8211; iOS Touch ID, iOS Face ID, Fingerprints, Windows Hello</h3>
<p>Biometric authentication, including <a href="https://docs.vmware.com/en/VMware-Horizon-Client-for-iOS/5.1/horizon-client-ios-installation/GUID-F1848930-0D37-484E-9A86-20FEDA7F62E3.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Touch ID</a>, <a href="https://docs.vmware.com/en/VMware-Horizon-Client-for-iOS/5.1/horizon-client-ios-installation/GUID-30545D82-DA80-47FF-8CB2-AC87B4EBC16A.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Face ID</a>, <a href="https://docs.vmware.com/en/VMware-Horizon-Client-for-Android/5.1/horizon-client-android-installation/GUID-434E1028-A9E7-462D-9FFD-9150A3F7DFFC.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Fingerprints</a>, and <a href="https://docs.vmware.com/en/VMware-Horizon-Client-for-Windows-10-UWP/5.1/horizon-client-windows-10uwp-installation/GUID-7731C7B7-E8C8-4DFF-939F-4DA844D2F089.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Windows Hello</a>, is disabled by default. To enable: (source = vDelboy &#8211; <a href="https://vdelboysview.com/2015/09/08/how-to-enable-touch-id-in-vmware-horizon-6-2/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">How to Enable Touch ID in VMware Horizon 6.2</a>Â andÂ <a href="https://docs.vmware.com/en/VMware-Horizon-7/7.10/horizon-administration/GUID-02404EBB-0578-4046-93A6-D57CABA1A8F9.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Configure Biometric Authentication</a> at VMware Docs)</p>
<ol>
<li>On the Horizon Connection Server, run <strong>ADSI Edit</strong>.</li>
<li>Right-click <strong>ADSI Edit</strong> and click <strong>Connect toâ€¦</strong></li>
<li>Change the first selection to <strong>Select or type a Distinguished Name</strong> and enter <strong>dc=vdi,dc=vmware,dc=int.</strong></li>
<li>Change the second selection to <strong>Select or type a domain or server</strong> and enter <strong>localhost</strong>. Click <strong>OK</strong>.</li>
<li>Navigate to <strong>Properties &gt; Global</strong>. On the right, double-click <strong>CN=Common</strong>.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10731 " src="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7db396670.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7db396670.png?w=510&amp;ssl=1 510w, https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7db396670.png?resize=300%2C294&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 510px) 100vw, 510px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Find the attribute <strong>pae-ClientConfig</strong> and double-click it.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10734 " src="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7e2a8a9b5.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7e2a8a9b5.png?w=400&amp;ssl=1 400w, https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7e2a8a9b5.png?resize=300%2C219&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Enter the line <strong><code>BioMetricsTimeout=-1</code></strong>, and click <strong>Add</strong>. Click <strong>OK</strong>. The change takes effect immediately.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10735 " src="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7e4b8f8a9.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7e4b8f8a9.png?w=362&amp;ssl=1 362w, https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/img_58ce7e4b8f8a9.png?resize=300%2C153&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 362px) 100vw, 362px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
</ol>
