<h4 id="toolboxcertificate">Toolbox Certificate</h4>
<p>Horizon Toolbox comes with a self-signed certificate. It can be replaced by doing the following:</p>
<ol>
<li>Copy a certificate .pfx file to <strong>C:\Program Files\VMware\HorizonToolbox\HorizonToolbox7.4\conf</strong>.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21282 " src="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/img_5a64819a8e5ef.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/img_5a64819a8e5ef.png?w=755&amp;ssl=1 755w, https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/img_5a64819a8e5ef.png?resize=300%2C165&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 755px) 100vw, 755px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Edit the file <strong>server.</strong><strong>xml</strong> thatâ€™s in the same <strong>conf</strong> folder. Make sure your text editor is elevated (as administrator).<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21283 " src="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/img_5a6481a98fc56.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/img_5a6481a98fc56.png?w=746&amp;ssl=1 746w, https://i0.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/img_5a6481a98fc56.png?resize=300%2C171&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 746px) 100vw, 746px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>In your text editor, do the following:
<ol>
<li>Scroll down to the <strong>&lt;Connector port=&#8221;18443&#8243;</strong> section (near line 85).</li>
<li>Change the <strong>keystoreFile</strong> attribute to the name of your .pfx file.</li>
<li>Change the <strong>keystorePass</strong> attribute to the password for your .pfx file.</li>
<li>Add a new attribute <code><strong>keystoreType="PKCS12"</strong></code></li>
</ol>
</li>
<li>Close and save the file.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21284 " src="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/img_5a64821747b07.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/img_5a64821747b07.png?w=842&amp;ssl=1 842w, https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/img_5a64821747b07.png?resize=300%2C122&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/img_5a64821747b07.png?resize=768%2C313&amp;ssl=1 768w" sizes="(max-width: 842px) 100vw, 842px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Restart the <strong>Apache Tomcat 8.5 Tomcat8</strong> service.<br/>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-18666 " src="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/img_59be8ad3d8fc0.png?w=1100" alt="" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/img_59be8ad3d8fc0.png?w=508&amp;ssl=1 508w, https://i2.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/img_59be8ad3d8fc0.png?resize=300%2C190&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 508px) 100vw, 508px" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
<li>Point your browser to <a href="https://view.corp.local:18443/toolbox">https://view.corp.local:18443/toolbox</a>Â and there should be no certificate error. Note: it takes several seconds for the toolbox Tomcat service to start; you can watch it in Task Manager.<br/>
<img src="https://i1.wp.com/www.carlstalhood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/bfad18568e4b02faf424f3326f195efe.png?w=1100" alt="" data-recalc-dims="1"/></li>
</ol>
