								February 18, 2020 at 10:29 am							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Hi Carl.   Just wanted to thank you for your very informative blog. I setup horizon a year ago here at my work. If it weren&#8217;t for your blog i would have probably been stuck many a times had to had to depend on the vmware&#8217;s website and kb articles. I seriously think they were made by robots for robots. Your in depth explainations have made even upgrading the environment painless whereas reading on vmware horizon how to upgrade they make it sound like everything is going to break . Your step by step visual documentation is a life saver.  Thank you so much.. I have become a huge fan of your knowledge.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='https://www.carlstalhood.com/vmware-horizon-7-connection-server/?replytocom=13730#respond' data-commentid="13730" data-postid="3285" data-belowelement="div-comment-13730" data-respondelement="respond" aria-label='Reply to Juan Lopez'>Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
