					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/7802c7e42dba0e0ffa7576d7d37dc314?s=56&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/7802c7e42dba0e0ffa7576d7d37dc314?s=112&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-56 photo' height='56' width='56'/>						<b class="fn">Carl Stalhood</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.carlstalhood.com/vmware-horizon-7-connection-server/comment-page-2/#comment-13477">
							<time datetime="2020-01-10T08:26:31-06:00">
								January 10, 2020 at 8:26 am							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Every Active Directory domain has a NetBIOS name in addition to it&#8217;s DNS name. When you log into windows, you typically enter NetBIOS_Domain\username. The domain&#8217;s DNS name is typically only used for UPN logins.</p>
<p>Note: computer names are also NetBIOS names, which is why they need to be 15 characters or less.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

